  "rawMarkdown" : "---\nsource: https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/SwiftUI\/ColorMatrix\ncrawled: 2025-12-02T17:37:25Z\n---\n\n# ColorMatrix\n\n**Structure**\n\nA matrix to use in an RGBA color transformation.\n\n## Declaration\n\n```swift\n@frozen struct ColorMatrix\n```\n\n## Overview\n\nThe matrix has five columns, each with a red, green, blue, and alpha component. You can use the matrix for tasks like creating a color transformation [doc:\/\/com.apple.SwiftUI\/documentation\/SwiftUI\/GraphicsContext\/Filter] for a [doc:\/\/com.apple.SwiftUI\/documentation\/SwiftUI\/GraphicsContext] using the [doc:\/\/com.apple.SwiftUI\/documentation\/SwiftUI\/GraphicsContext\/Filter\/colorMatrix(_:)] method.\n\n## Creating an identity matrix\n\n- **init()**: Creates the identity matrix.\n\n## First column\n\n- **r1**\n- **g1**\n- **b1**\n- **a1**\n\n## Second column\n\n- **r2**\n- **g2**\n- **b2**\n- **a2**\n\n## Third column\n\n- **r3**\n- **g3**\n- **b3**\n- **a3**\n\n## Fourth column\n\n- **r4**\n- **g4**\n- **b4**\n- **a4**\n\n## Fifth column\n\n- **r5**\n- **g5**\n- **b5**\n- **a5**\n\n## Applying blur and shadows\n\n- **blur(radius:opaque:)**: Applies a Gaussian blur to this view.\n- **shadow(color:radius:x:y:)**: Adds a shadow to this view.\n\n## Conforms To\n\n- BitwiseCopyable\n- Copyable\n- Equatable\n- Sendable\n- SendableMetatype\n\n",
